{"TopicId":147490,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Totally embarrassed","CreatedByName":"Boba Kerman Fett","CreatedById":168617,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-12T03:02:52Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Boba Kerman Fett","CreatedById":168617,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-12T03:02:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey there. \u00A0I DONT KNOW SHOOT ABOUT COMPUTERS...having\u00A0said that I became hooked on this game through PS4. What a disaster! Im current looking for a computer to\u00A0just play this game. Please can anyone tell me if these specs will be good enough to run KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks in advance.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSystem: AMD FX-4300 3.80GHZ Quad-Core | AMD 760G Chipset | 8GB DDR3 | 1TB HDD | Genuine Windows 10 Home 64-bit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGraphics: AMD Radeon R7 240 2GB Video Card | 24X DVD\u00B1RW Dual-Layer Drive | Audio: 7.1 Channel | Gigabit LAN | Keyboard and Mouse\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConnectivity: 6x USB 2.0 | 1x RJ-45 Network Ethernet 10/100/1000 | Audio | 1x HDMI | 1x DVI | 1x VGA\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-12T03:54:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom the KSP store:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRecommended System Specs:\u003Cbr\u003E\n* 2.0Ghz Dual Core CPU or higher (preferably higher)\u003Cbr\u003E\n* 4GB RAM\u003Cbr\u003E\n* 512MB Video Card, Shader Model 3.0\u003Cbr\u003E\n* 4GB Free HD space\u003Cbr\u003E\n* Windows Vista, 7, 8 or 10\u003Cbr\u003E\n* An Intel-based Mac running Mac OS X 10.8 or higher\u003Cbr\u003E\n* A Debian based Linux distro\u003Cbr\u003E\n* Chromebooks are NOT SUPPORTED\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"legoclone09","CreatedById":142607,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-12T06:46:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPersonally, I\u0027d look on PC Part Picker at some of the build guides they have there. Personally, I run an Intel i5 4760k, 8GB DDR3 RAM, and a GTX 760 w/ 4GB DDR5 vRAM. It runs great with lots of visual mods.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal101","CreatedById":157058,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-12T20:35:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe machine you listed will do just nicely sir.\u003Cbr\u003E\nFX-43xx is reasonably fast quad-module cpu (but might also look at i3-3220 as a better alternative for about same money though) the video card is somewhat weak - I suggest either RX 470 (or half weaker RX 460) from AMD cards, or GTX 1060 (or half weaker GTX 960).\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlso I would make sure that Power Supply is not a \u0022no-name\u0022 one, but one of Corsair, FSP, Seasonic, Cooler Master, Enermax or similar.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI prefer Debian Linux (SolydK) , but Windows might do fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-16T10:05:36Z\u0022 title=\u002209/16/2016 10:05  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 16, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbal101\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-30T01:08:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCriminey your machine makes mine look like a TI-83 calculator!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ultimate Steve","CreatedById":161505,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-30T01:43:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222780482\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147490\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentty