nts\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.google.com/url?sa=i\u0026amp;rct=j\u0026amp;q=\u0026amp;esrc=s\u0026amp;source=images\u0026amp;cd=\u0026amp;cad=rja\u0026amp;uact=8\u0026amp;ved=0ahUKEwjajNOt-7XPAhXG6CYKHeMbAiYQjRwIBw\u0026amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fforum.kerbalspaceprogram.com%2Findex.php%3F%2Ftopic%2F120709-kerbal-space-program-is-coming-to-the-ti-83-calculator%2F\u0026amp;psig=AFQjCNGuA2cPTKg3l_XK1QzNzW9_mttlmg\u0026amp;ust=1475286150247830\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Image result for ksp on ti-83 calculator\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022446\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/jqXD1rg.png\u0022 style=\u0022margin-top:0px;\u0022 width=\u0022360\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm. This might actually work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want that calculator.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-30T12:40:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://hackaday.com/2016/05/31/kerbal-space-program-for-the-apple-ii/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EI\u0027ll just leave this here...\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I will recommend that if you can, try KSP on a memory stick on the computer you want to buy \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MachTurtle","CreatedById":153223,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-30T23:00:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222780517\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147490\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221475199836\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161505\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ultimate Steve\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, Ultimate Steve said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.google.com/url?sa=i\u0026amp;rct=j\u0026amp;q=\u0026amp;esrc=s\u0026amp;source=images\u0026amp;cd=\u0026amp;cad=rja\u0026amp;uact=8\u0026amp;ved=0ahUKEwjajNOt-7XPAhXG6CYKHeMbAiYQjRwIBw\u0026amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fforum.kerbalspaceprogram.com%2Findex.php%3F%2Ftopic%2F120709-kerbal-space-program-is-coming-to-the-ti-83-calculator%2F\u0026amp;psig=AFQjCNGuA2cPTKg3l_XK1QzNzW9_mttlmg\u0026amp;ust=1475286150247830\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Image result for ksp on ti-83 calculator\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022446\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/jqXD1rg.png\u0022 style=\u0022margin-top:0px;\u0022 width=\u0022360\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm. This might actually work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes anyone else here remember keying a lunar lander game into their programmable calculator? I\u0027m talking about one with numeric display only (I had an HP-33C) where you input a thrust setting and it calculates a new velocity, altitude, and remaining fuel. It was like a one-D KSP, though the sim speed was around 30 seconds per frame rather than 30 frames per second. I hadn\u0027t thought about that in 35 years!\u00A0 Does that make me geezer?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hpmuseum.org/software/33smoonl.htm\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EI found the source code!\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002233c3q.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.hpmuseum.org/3qs/33c3q.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-30T23:03:01Z\u0022 title=\u002209/30/2016 11:03  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by MachTurtle\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EAdded historical source code and photo.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-01T09:41:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*sigh* rpn ... that reminds me of several versions of shooting oneself in the foot in various programming languages ... :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe PC-config is fine.\u003Cs\u003E If you plan to run Linux i\u0027d take a nvidia graphics card. \u003C/s\u003EWindows.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-01T09:42:38Z\u0022 title=\u002210/01/2016 09:42  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 1, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Green Baron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}